 This maybe a useful item for the Library Section?<br>
<br>
     ------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
  I Resisted the Stun about 8 or so times, the Fear a bit less, had higher PR than MR maybe why? Both have an HUGE HUGE radius. Was stunned and Feared much of the time 40-50%? Had about 190 PR and 170 MR, really vicious Fear/stun effcts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
  PETS: I had warned folk to back pets off at first due to fear. Water pets are a MUST for this job, it's not how much damage they do/take it's how much they aren't STUNNED. I can't be sure how good my pet worked because I was generally stunned/feared 50% of the time, but I was Summoned pretty early when I personally had done nothing ergo the pet must have racked up some damage and I had left /pet taunt on, doh! but pets shouldn't be able to taunt at all on Sev? Managed to turn /pet taunt off when I saw Jibober at my side at one point. Problem is pets have very poor MR, next time pets must be SOWed and have resist magic cast on them.<br>
<br>
 -- Anyone know how well their pets have meleed Severilous? --<br>
<br>
  Kept seeing them running out and in. Pet stayed alive all through the fight, mine had lost about 20% of its health. Pets also will find their way back to the target automatically and won't get lost like we will. This is a Good Thing (tm) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
  Sev killed me when he was down to a sliver of health, (why do dragons ALWAYS DO THAT?! Can't they let me run away for once? bah :&gt;) The pets were still there fighting when I went down but only Galestorm (our monk) and about 4 other folk were left close to him that I could see.<br>
<br>
  When Sev got way down I /ooc for folk to charge in because i was trying to stay close to moonitor it all. I got in close and was meleeing him to check distance, hit him 3 times, woot! 1 hp each! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  I got off approximately 8 Scars of Sigil (fire) and 4 Shock of Spikes (magic) TOTAL RESISTS FROM MELEE RANGE! I had the same report from all mages. Frankly mages should NOT nuke it's a waste of time and gets us killed to no effect. We should instead gather together just out of range and nuke adds. We stay alive pets stay alive. Can't have it both ways, nuking him is pointless if you're a mage.<br>
<br>
  The fear and AOE and running folk and pets brought a mass of adds. <br>
<br>
               --IMPORTANT QUESTION-- <br>
  Did the adds aggro on Sev at all? Saw one pet and couple of folk fighting adds. The number of adds keeped seeming to decrease so either folk or Sev were killing them. Anyone know if the adds wil aggro on Sev?<br>
<br>
  Healers coudln't heal cause of stun Fear. Really need to set up an &quot;aid station&quot; just out of range of the AOEs so tanks can come running for help, and casters for gems. I dropped malachite at our original site so when I died I ran from FoB but of course the malachite was gone, I was half way to scene when Sev reported as killed.<br>
<br>
    -- My conclusions for future Sev raids--<br>
<br>
1) Mages and water pets are needed (info is needed on how well they were fighting/not stunned if possible, if water pets don't get stunned that's a HUGE bonus). Please buff the pets with SOW, Magic Resistance and other buffs but NOT haste spells <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
2) Mages can summon 5MR and 5PR daggers for ranged slots if needed.<br>
3) Mages can't nuke Sev, so they should nuke adds and DS the tanks.<br>
4) Casters should set up nearby so that folk can come to get healed and /loc be shouted to those who are feared as to where to gather (it's a huge foggy outdoor zone for those who don't know).<br>
5) Walking/running has no effect on Sev's Fear so all should be SOWed anyway so tey can't get back quick.<br>
6) Adds are horrendous info is needed on whether they aggroed Sev or us more. Clearing them would take to much time except for those in immediate area before fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lastly<br>
<br>
